Description: The Flight into Egypt: a night piece; the Virgin seated on a donkey holding the Christ Child, while St Joseph leads the way towards the left while holding a lantern; third state with shading added in drypoint to the figures of the Virgin, Joseph and the donkey, to the ground, and lower part of sky, before additional shading of highlights in upper corners and in lower right foreground. 1651 Etching, burin and drypoint Watermark: Foolscap with five-pointed collar (probably Hinterding catalogue, variant E.b., datable 1651)
Curator's comments: For comment and an impression of first state see also F,4.103.
